Make an overview of the legacy html pages, not generated by doxygen as a result of scanning .h and/or .cc files, and link them to a unique name and input file.

The legacy doxygen generated html web pages are given in $PLANROOT/current_objective/reference-manual
for read-only purposes only.

It was generated from a doc/ directory for which a backup was stored in $PLANROOT/current_objective/legacy-doc
also for read-only purposes only.

The overview must be written to $PLANROOT/current_objective/legacy-overview.md

For example,

reference-manual/group__book__writing__intro.html is such a page.

It was generated from writing_intro.dox, the page is associated with the group `book_writing_intro`,
which can also be seen from the html file's name. Therefore in the legacy-overview.md the following
entry must be listed:

TAG                     INPUT                   OUTPUT                                  TITLE
book_writing_intro      writing_intro.dox       group__book__writing__intro.html        Writing Debug Output: Introduction

Note that also contains writing_intro.dox:
```
\page page_writing_into
\ingroup book_writing_intro

\section section_writing_into_introduction Introduction
```

but there is no html page containing the string 'into' (a typo of course, but that's what it contains) or 'page.*writing' for that matter,
and the content of writing_intro.dox appears only in group__book__writing__intro.html - no other page is associated with it.
